{"cursor":"11275","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":" lizard using camouflage to avoid detection in Bandipur National Park.]]\n\n\n\n\n\nIn ecology, 'crypsis' is the ability of an organism to avoid observation or\ndetection by other organisms. It may be either a predation strategy or an\nantipredator adaptation, and methods include camouflage, nocturnality,\nlifestyle, transparency, and mimicry. The word can also\nbe used in the context of eggs and pheromone\nproduction. Crypsis can in principle involve visual,\nolfactory or auditory camouflage.\n","linknr":373,"url":"Crypsis","recorded":1362482857,"links":39,"instances":["optics","genus","biology"],"pdf":["http://www-eve.ucdavis.edu/stachowicz/papers/Hultgren_Stachowicz_2011_BookChapter.pdf","http://www-eve.ucdavis.edu/stachowicz/papers/Hultgren_Stachowicz_2011_BookChapter.pdf"],"categories":["Ethology","Mimicry","Biological interactions","Antipredator adaptations","Predation","Camouflage"],"headings":["Overview","Varieties of crypsis","Effects","Gallery","See also","References","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/79/2005-Draco-indochinensis.jpg/220px-2005-Draco-indochinensis.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/d/d7/Brtish_dpm2.jpg/100px-Brtish_dpm2.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/20/Jumping_spider_with_prey.jpg/250px-Jumping_spider_with_prey.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/82/Agama_aculeata.jpg/120px-Agama_aculeata.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bc/LeafShapedGrasshopper.JPG/120px-LeafShapedGrasshopper.JPG","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b5/Leaf-nosed_viper.jpg/120px-Leaf-nosed_viper.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/19/Camouflage_DSC05383_-_Original_image.JPG/120px-Camouflage_DSC05383_-_